description.content:
 This endpoint streamlines metadata creation for multiple documents.
 Documents are stored at primaryLocation, secondaryLocation, and tertiaryLocation,
 associated with the provided documentType. If no documentType is specified,
 the system assigns the Unclassified DocumentType to the document.
 In instances where the specified location names are absent in Dynamic Docs,
 they are automatically generated, and the document is stored in these newly established locations.
 The endpoint returns a new DocumentBatchId, corresponding to a list of fileUploadIds,
 which can be utilized to initiate a file upload request.

 The Request Metadata includes The Location hierachy and it's own attributes and a list
 of documents that includes DocumentName with extension, the DocumentType and a list of DocumentAttributes

 ```json
 {
   "primaryLocation": {
     "name": "Example Name",
     "attributes": [
       {
         "name": "Example Location Attribute",
         "value": "Example Attribute Value"
       }
     ]
   },
   "secondaryLocation": {
     "name": "Example Name",
     "attributes": [
       {
         "name": "Example Location Attribute",
         "value": "Example Attribute Value"
       }
     ]
   },
   "tertiaryLocation": {
     "name": "Example Name",
     "attributes": [
       {
         "name": "Example Location Attribute",
         "value": "Example Attribute Value"
       }
     ]
   },
   "documents": [
    {
      "name": "Name.pdf",
      "documentType": "Example Document Type",
      "attributes": [
        {
          "type": "Alphanumeric",
          "name": "Example Attribute Name",
          "value": "Example Attribute Value",
         "length": 50
        }
      ]
    }
   ]
 }
```

 This endpoint allows the upload of a single document to Dynamic Docs, supporting two workflows:

 **Workflow 1:**
 If the **Metadata** parameter contains information, the document will be stored in the specified location
 with the provided document type. If the provided document attributes or location names do not exist in
 Dynamic Docs, they will be automatically created, and the document will be stored in the newly created
 locations. The endpoint will return a **documentId** that specifies the document ID in the final location.

 **Metadata** example:
 ```json
{
   "documentType": "Example Document Type",
   "documentAttributes": [
      {
         "type": "Alphanumeric",
         "name": "Example Attribute Name",
         "value": "Example Attribute Value",
         "length": 50
      }
   ],
   "primaryLocation": {
      "name": "Example Name",
      "attributes": [
         {
            "name": "Example Location Attribute",
            "value": "Example Attribute Value"
         }
      ]
   },
   "secondaryLocation": {
      "name": "Example Name",
      "attributes": [
         {
            "name": "Example Location Attribute",
            "value": "Example Attribute Value"
         }
      ]
   },
   "tertiaryLocation": {
      "name": "Example Name",
      "attributes": [
         {
            "name": "Example Location Attribute",
            "value": "Example Attribute Value"
         }
      ]
   }
}
```
 **Workflow 2:**
 If the **Metadata** parameter is empty, the document will be uploaded to a **staging location** without
 specific attributes or location assignments. This is particularly useful when the final location of the document has not yet been determined.
 You can use the `PUT /documents/{staged_document_id}/move-from-staging` endpoint later to assign the
 location, document type and attributes. As a result, the endpoint will return a **stagedDocumentId** that specifies the
 document ID inside the staging location.

 Please note that **documentId** and **stagedDocumentId** are distinct values.

 If the `Microsoft Computer Vision - OCR` module is enabled, the document will undergo automatic Optical Character Recognition (OCR).

